# repos.txt — repos covered by gh-runner-toggle, one "owner/name [count]" per line.
#
# Copy this to `repos.txt` (which is gitignored) and add your repos, or just run:
#   grt add <owner/repo>
# which appends here and opens the runs-on toggle PR.
#
# The optional count = how many runner instances to run for that repo
# (default 1). Use 2+ so a workflow's parallel jobs actually run in parallel
# instead of queueing on a single runner.
#
# The optional `docker` token mounts the host Docker socket into that repo's
# runners so docker-building jobs (e.g. `cdk deploy` with container image
# assets) work self-hosted. OPT-IN ONLY: it hands that repo's CI control of
# Docker on this PC (root-equivalent) — grant per repo you trust end-to-end.
#
# Lines starting with # and blank lines are ignored. Private repos only.
#
# owner/example-repo
# owner/busy-repo 2
# owner/docker-deploy-repo 2 docker
